     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="31"/>
   <head>❧ The Authors peraswasion from proofe laying the totall some of the Booke.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>LOng griefe by many chāges taught,</l>
      <l>the authors p<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>n to write:</l>
      <l>This same poore vndigested much</l>
      <l>so take the widd<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>w<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>s my<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>e<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>
      </l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>The dayes and times bee wea<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="2 letters">
            <desc>••</desc>
         </gap>nes,</l>
      <l>by heauy conceipts weight:</l>
      <l>The mery neuer thinke time long,</l>
      <l>such is affections sleight.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>But to preuent that by no change,</l>
      <l>thy <gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>ime may tast for long:</l>
      <l>Prepare thy thoughts to ioy in smart,</l>
      <l>a preparation strong.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>In sadnes dwell, and stable rule,</l>
      <l>hold fast and euer feare.</l>
      <l>That natures sleights by plaine deceipt</l>
      <l>away all by will weare.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>So thus thou wading feedest still,</l>
      <l>vpon desired ende:</l>
      <l>With patience: and ioyst to see,</l>
      <l>how thy twist length doth spend.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>For truely vaine delights which passe,</l>
      <l>thy time as neuer weary:</l>
      <l>May nature feede, as for the stanle,</l>
      <l>ne making spirit cheary.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>There is so strange a difference,</l>
      <l>twixt nature and thy grace:</l>
      <l>That where the sences ioy euen most,</l>
      <l>sure there is snaring place.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>For sences doe but nature reach,</l>
      <l>but spirit truth aspires:</l>
      <l>For this: the Mr. wages giues,</l>
      <l>vaine bee all other hiers.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>The kingdome violence suffer doth,</l>
      <l>and violence is in oyd:</l>
      <l>All entermission is plaine losse,</l>
      <l>and doth thy hold destroy.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Pray therefore for beleeuing hurt,</l>
      <l>and combates crown<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap> ettaine:</l>
      <l>Abandoning affections fraudes,</l>
      <l>whose ende is euer vaine.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>For ease and rest as maine deceipts,</l>
      <l>preuaile with most m<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>n much:</l>
      <l>But mariage garment neuer lot,</l>
      <l>is sorted vnto such.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>O that thou knewst how sweet a thing.</l>
      <l>ta sleepe in Iesus armes.</l>
      <l>Nature should nest of vipers east,</l>
      <l>and den of hugest harmes.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Experience reporteth.</l>
      <l>Obedience preuaileth.</l>
      <l>Faith conquereth.</l>
   </lg>
   <trailer>FINIS.</trailer>
